      </p>
      <p class="premise">
        Sabbianera, 1600s. Fiammetta, a one-eyed peasant woman trapped in a brutal marriage, has spent three years secretly buying and restoring a galleon hidden behind the witch-rocks of a Sardinian cove. Her crew is the women her village dismissed: a quartermaster who reads, a sailor who can rig a ship in her sleep, and Stellina Frangipane – the noble's six-year-old daughter, who emits a faint blue glow whenever she's near the cursed Spanish doubloons forged from New World gold. Their target: the lost treasure of the legendary pirate Calogero Sauro, buried on a forgotten island. Their problem: Stellina's father has just promised her in marriage to a Spanish-collaborator noble who's heard about the gold. They have one week.
      </p>
      <p class="premise">
